http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/CPIM-told-to-clarify-stand-on-Lavalin-case/article14002717.ece

Kerala Pradesh Congress Committee (KPCC) president V.M. Sudheeran has asked the CPI(M) national leadership to clarify its stand on the multi-crore SNC-Lavalin corruption case involving party Polit Bureau member Pinarayi Vijayan against the backdrop of the High Court observation that there is substance in the points put forth by the State government in the sensitive case.Talking to media persons here on Saturday, Mr. Sudheeran said the Left party was bound to clarify its stand as the court had made the observation on a petition filed by the State government through Director General of Prosecutions T. Asaf Ali seeking early hearing of the revision petitions filed by the CBI and others challenging the CBI special court order scrapping the whole corruption case. Mr. Sudheeran was in the district as part of his ongoing Janaraksha Yatra.